<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Shinu:
[B]being a guild leader, and a cleric, I make damn sure my costs are covered. even so sometimes I cut it slim (usually have a bank acct of under 1k).. because a) I hate selling junk so I give it away to someone who needs and b) I just don't do alot that makes for high cash loot often. I spend all my time grouping with friends, so its never an issue that I loot to cover my costs. I was in a semi-pickup group the other night in hs, at least the leader was someone I didn't know. and I said point blank, you will give me gems and stuff to pay for peridot. no problem by them. it is my honest opinion that peridot symbols are very worth the money, even on non raid scale events. it just depends *who* I'm going to cast on. priorities: puller, main tank, chanter, cleric, other tanks. if we're fairly safe, I may just do a symbol on the puller/tank. if its a nasty raid, I'll keep most of us symboled always. ya, it eats the bank acct, but those extra cpl hundred hp can save lives, and thus time and hassle.

Shinu
Evil Priestess of the 58th thingymabob
Silent Shadow
Quellious[/B][/QUOTE]

