<P>
<FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#FF0000">*If HTML and/or <A HREF="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/ubbcode.html" target=_blank>UBB Code</A> are enabled, this means you can use HTML and/or UBB Code in your message.</FONT>
<br>
<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">electrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I'm curious if anyone is in a guild that has a policy to help out those who have reoccuring spell reagent costs.  We're doing a lot of raiding in my guild, and its starting to take a heavy toll on my bank account.  I'm getting very few trips to Sebilis, since we're raiding so much.<P>A lot of it is for people's epic weapons.  I'm proposing that those raids, the beneficiary of the raid should supply the reagents to the clerics, enchanters and mages.<P>But I'd like to uncover any novel policies or procedures and recommend them to my own guild.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kannayyan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Im only 26th but I have been told that all gems looted on raids, and donations, etc should be given to clerics to compensate....just make sure you have a chanter buy your reagents for you, or if you must do it yourself, get a shammy cha buff and carry a few xtra cha items in your inv....This, I feel, will be a never ending problem for a cleric, however, you can camp a few hours in zones like skyfire or bw, higher level zones that require no groups, mostly solo classes, to rezz for donations and more than pay for the loss  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Windalyn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My guild does not cover the cost of peridots for any raids unless normal gems drop, which are divided among the clerics.  The exception to this is hate when all cash loot goes to the wizzards for port gems. They even give one rare gem to all monks and wizzards as a thank you for coming.  <P>Due to this I can end up using about 5k plat a month on peridots. However a few good friends I have in the guild do realize this, and make sure that at least once a week we go to Sebilis.  One night camping the jail there can end up with 1k plat in gems easily.  So I can for the most part keep up with the demand on peridots. <P>I have tried to get some kind of reimbursement on raids before, but this never works.  As an enchanter friend once asked  me upon seeing another guild cleric's bank account...<BR> <BR>"Do they make clerics take a vow of poverty or what?"   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Windalyn Spirithealer<BR>55 Templar of Tunare<BR>Bertoxxulous <P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Georgia_TKR</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My guild believes it is the responsibility of the cleric to contribute peridots to the raids rather than the guild pay the clerics for the peridot costs.<P>I never use peridots on raids unless they pay for them  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> touché<P>------------------<BR>Georgia Gaelicmyst<BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR>Everlore Staff Member<BR>http://www.everlore.com/</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Georgia_TKR:<BR><B>My guild believes it is the responsibility of the cleric to contribute peridots to the raids rather than the guild pay the clerics for the peridot costs.<P>I never use peridots on raids unless they pay for them   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> touché<BR></B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Time to find another guild. My guild, and even alot of pick up groups, give me all gem/jewelery drops. It's standard procedure on Xegony these days.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aean</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">heheh i was in the warrens the other day with my 18 cleric and was grouped with a rogue. After a few kills the rogue suddenly says "clerics get all the gems, loot this one" and i do. There was a Cat's Eye Agate on it hahaha I was completely flattered <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> and he is now on my friends list <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Xitara Du'Vie -Xegony-</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My guild has recently been collecting a lot of equipment that nobody would use, so we have decided to sell some of it off to other players in order to pay for gems/coffins etc.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tommara</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yes, it's also my guild's practice to give quick cash items, notably gems, except for high ticket items like diamonds, to clerics in the group/raid.  My guildmates also contribute peridots and/or cash on an individual basis.<P>I've only joined in once to help out on an epic (my cleric's been semi-retired for awhile, and only recently been playing a lot) and the enchantress who it was for handed me a stack of peridots at the beginning of the raid.<P>When I first raised the issue (many had no idea how much peridots cost), we discussed establishing a guild fund for this sort of thing, but ultimately decided that it wouldn't be fair to folks who had gained no benefit from whatever raid required peridot symbols.  It's since worked out pretty well, with the added side-benefit, now that my guildmates are more aware of the cost, of being encouraged to use Pinzarn instead for routine stuff.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P><P>------------------<BR>Tommara, Level 53 Vicar<BR>Tommar, Level 40 Ranger<BR>Povar</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Meddik</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I am lucky enough to be in a circle of friends that know to help everyone cover expenses. This includes all the guilds I regularly group with or raid with. =)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Resurrector</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If your guild won't pay for peridot regants on raids (or help you with a seb gem run/whatever) then they suck. So leave that guild and find a better one.<P>Or tell your guild mates that only the people who give you pp/periodots get the buff.<P>Eithor will solve your problem.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P><BR>Resurrector<BR>Cleric of the 57th (Veeshan)<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wamsutta</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Our guild (The Guardian Lords from Povar server) has an extensive guild treasury.  On a guild-sponsored raid all non-rollable items are sold by a designated treasurer and that cash is used to replace the stock of reagents used for the raid (eg portal gems, buffing gems).  <P>Very detailed logs are kept by the treasurer and made available on the guild web site.  Our guild GM decides what qualifies as a guild-sponsored raid (ie normal nightly outings do not qualify).<P>Wamsutta<BR>54th Templar of Povar</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">electrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Some classes have virtually no costs and a number of benefits from raids, the option to roll on loot that drops during the raid.  I'd almost be for proposing a raid entrance fee of 6 peridots per person, waved for those who have regeant costs.<P>Or the other thing that occurred to me was that if you win a lotto you have to chip in, oh, 100-200p to the reagent fund.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Khaidu Ilkhanate</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">(Oops double post)<p>[This message has been edited by Khaidu Ilkhanate (edited 03-25-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Khaidu Ilkhanate</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My guild does big guild raids just about everynight, every couple raids all the clerics and enchanters are handed a few stacks of peridots, payed for by the extra loot we get being auctioned off by our guild trader   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Khaidu Ilkhanate<BR>Templar of Talisman <A HREF="http://www.norrath.org" TARGET=_blank>www.norrath.org</A> <BR><p>[This message has been edited by Khaidu Ilkhanate (edited 03-25-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Shinu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">being a guild leader, and a cleric, I make damn sure my costs are covered. even so sometimes I cut it slim (usually have a bank acct of under 1k).. because a) I hate selling junk so I give it away to someone who needs and b) I just don't do alot that makes for high cash loot often. I spend all my time grouping with friends, so its never an issue that I loot to cover my costs. I was in a semi-pickup group the other night in hs, at least the leader was someone I didn't know. and I said point blank, you will give me gems and stuff to pay for peridot. no problem by them. it is my honest opinion that peridot symbols are very worth the money, even on non raid scale events. it just depends *who* I'm going to cast on. priorities: puller, main tank, chanter, cleric, other tanks. if we're fairly safe, I may just do a symbol on the puller/tank. if its a nasty raid, I'll keep most of us symboled always. ya, it eats the bank acct, but those extra cpl hundred hp can save lives, and thus time and hassle.<P>Shinu<BR>Evil Priestess of the 58th thingymabob<BR>Silent Shadow<BR>Quellious<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thistleburr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Greetings!<P>My guildleader hands me 4 or 5 stacks of peridots a week. I cover the cost of emeralds, star rubies, and pearls myself.<P>10 hours in Veeshan's Peak, 113 peridots.<P>------------------<BR><B>Thistleburr</B>, High Priestess of Bristlebane<BR><A HREF="http://www.the-elitists.com" TARGET=_blank><I>The Elitists</I></A>, Tribunal Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">electrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It seems like there's always a few people that get hit with costs that benefit the entire raid but they don't get reimbursed for.<P>Seems like there's a couple of ways to handle that:  <P>1. change a raid entrance fee to cover costs<BR>2. maintain a guild treasury<BR>3. charge a loot fee, if you win a lotto you pay Xpp to help defray the costs.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Llew Lifebringer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Maybe we're just lucky... During the blessing stage getting ready for Nagafen, everyone kept piping up "Oh, I've got a stack of <reagent> for the blessers."<P>At one point, one of the poor people said "Enough already, I don't have any more room in my bags!"<P>Encourage an ethic in your guild to have everyone bring a few of the needed items and throw them into the pot.   Keep everyone aware that along with whatever resist gear, they should bring a few peridots, or pearls, or whatever.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Scrune</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Saryrn for the most part gives all (non-rare) gems to their clerics for Peridots. I find alot of the time that I may gain double or even triple the amount of plat in gems than I actually used, but other times I will burn thru 40 Peridots on a raid and not get 1 damn thing, so I think it evens out.<P>Sometimes if I got a bank full of plat, a backpack full of Peridots and another backpack full of Rubies, Saphires, Fire Emeralds etc ... I will only take a portion of looted gems and ask that the rest be distributed out to the party.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Salina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Glory's Path frequently has members (good god, the other night one of my guys handed a BACKPACK FULL of peridots) donate peridots, or gems/loot from our escapades.<P>It's a well-established rule in my guild - if gems drop, they go to the clerics until the clerics have made what they expended in peridots.  The rest is split among everyone else.<P>None of my folks have a problem with this (they're hooked on Marzin).<P>------------------<BR>Salina Grey<BR>Erudite Templar of Pain, Bertoxxulous<BR>Guild Leader, Glory's Path</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Holywrathe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My main character is a guild leader on 7th hammer.<BR>I myself,and many others often purchase stacks of gems for clerics before we raid and I frequently keep a stack or 2 of peridots on me if I am xp grouping in Sebilis/karnors.<BR>In addition all cash loot (non-rare) gems that drop immediately become property of the guild organiser/group leader to divide amongst any clerics we are grouped with/raiding with.<BR>To me it seems unfair to expect you to contribute large amounts of personal cash to raids etc out of your own pocket,that's the way we operate anyhow.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Morrun</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My guild doesn't have any formal rules about subsidising our peridot habit (as one of our druids put it), but everyone is aware of how much it costs for that 650hp buff - so guildmates do contribute frequently to my inventory of peridots.  So I tend to be generous with Marzin.<P>There are some fun ways of raising cash at short notice: try doing an AE group in Mistmoore sometime with some high level casters.  Pulling the whole castle and then killing it in less than 30 seconds is quite a blast  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><BR><P>------------------<BR>Morrun Catspaw<BR>55th level Templar of Bristlebane<BR>Albion - Death Before Dishonour!<BR>Cazic-Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
